# Digital Clock

## Overview

Digital Clock is a simple web application that displays the current time and calculates a bill based on the elapsed time. The application is built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

## Features

- Displays the current time in hours, minutes, and seconds.
- Calculates a bill based on the elapsed time since the page was loaded.
- Styled with CSS for a visually appealing interface.

## Installation

To run the Digital Clock application locally, follow these steps:

1. Clone the repository to your local machine:  https://github.com/brook7G/Digital-Clock.git

2. Navigate to the project directory: `cd Digital-Clock`


3. Open the `index.html` file in your web browser.

## Usage

Once the application is running, you will see the current time displayed on the screen. The bill is calculated and updated every second based on the elapsed time since the page was loaded.

